---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Puppy Guide"
  description="Puppy Guide 50+ Pages, organized, with an Appindex. Easy to Go back and reference problems to solutions."
>
  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->

  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1
          class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight"
        >
          The Blueprint for a Calm Puppy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
          Stop guessing. Stop trying random training tips. Get the <strong
            >67-page guide</strong
          > that walks you through <strong>exactly what your puppy needs</strong
          > to grow into a confident, calm companion.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a
            href="#download"
            class="bg-yellow-500 hover:bg-yellow-600 text-gray-900 font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-lg transition transform hover:scale-105"
          >
            Get Your Free Guide
          </a>
          <a
            href="#what-inside"
            class="bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-lg border-2 border-gray-900 transition"
          >
            See What's Inside
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-red-50 py-16 px-8 rounded-2xl">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">
          Most Puppy Owners Are Doing It Wrong
        </h2>

        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-red-500 shadow-sm mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <strong>The Problem:</strong> You get advice on "sit" and "stay" — but
            nothing about the nervous system work that creates a <strong
              >calm puppy</strong
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">😰</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
              Your Puppy Panics When Alone
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              They haven't learned that separation is safe. Separation anxiety
              develops that takes years to fix.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🍽️</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Feeding Time Is Chaos</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              No calm routine. No structure. Your puppy jumps, begs, or develops
              resource guarding behaviors.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🚶</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
              Walks Feel Like Battles
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Pulling, lunging, inability to focus on you. Real-world chaos that
              training classes never prepared you for.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">⚡</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
              Your Puppy Is Always "On"
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              They can't regulate their nervous system. No calm default state.
              You're exhausted by 6 months.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-100 border-2 border-red-500 p-8 rounded-xl">
          <p class="text-xl text-red-900 font-bold">
            The Real Truth: <span class="block mt-2"
              >Behavior problems don't start at 6 months. They start on day one
              — with the foundation work you establish in the first 3 months.</span
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE SOLUTION -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
          What You Actually Need
        </h2>

        <div
          class="bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-10 mb-12 border-2 border-blue-200"
        >
          <div class="text-center mb-8">
            <div class="text-6xl mb-4">📖</div>
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
              The Complete Puppy Training Guide
            </h3>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-4">
              <strong>67 pages of exactly what your puppy needs</strong> to become
              calm, confident, and well-mannered.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 italic">
              Not another list of cute tricks. This is the nervous system work,
              structure, and real-world training that prevents behavior
              problems.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Three Column Value Props -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-green-500"
          >
            <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🧠</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              Nervous System Regulation
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Learn why "tire them out" is wrong — and what actually creates a
              calm puppy. The science-based approach to a puppy that can
              regulate themselves.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-blue-500"
          >
            <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🏗️</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              Foundation Structure
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Crate training, boundaries, routines, and communication that work
              everywhere — not just in your living room or training class.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-purple-500"
          >
            <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🎮</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              Game-Based Training
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Skip boring drills. Learn the games your puppy actually wants to
              play — that teach better than any command.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT'S INSIDE - TABLE OF CONTENTS -->
    <section id="what-inside" class="mb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
          What You Get Inside (67 Pages of Real Training)
        </h2>

        <!-- PHASE 1 -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-blue-100 p-8 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-blue-600 mb-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            🔵 PHASE 1: The Critical Window (8-12 Weeks)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 font-semibold">
            What Your Puppy's Brain Is Doing (And What You Must Build)
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6">
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Name Game Jackpot</strong> — How to make your name the best
              predictor of good things
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Find It Scatter</strong> — The sniffing game that teaches
              calm through neuroscience
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Confidence Building</strong> — Preventing fearfulness before
              it starts
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Critical Socialization</strong> — The right way to expose
              (hint: it's NOT "throw them in the deep end")
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>House Training Without Punishment</strong> — The only method
              that actually works
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- PHASE 2 -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-50 to-emerald-100 p-8 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-green-600 mb-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            🟢 PHASE 2: Building Confidence (12-16 Weeks)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 font-semibold">
            Turning Your Puppy Into a Problem-Solver
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6">
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Hide and Seek Recall</strong> — Recall that actually works
              (way better than calling "come")
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>The Sit Jackpot</strong> — Building impulse control through
              rewards, not punishment
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Bite Inhibition Training</strong> — Ensuring your puppy learns
              "soft mouth" safely
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Early Fear Period Management</strong> — Why your puppy suddenly
              gets scared (and what to do)
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Mouthing & Play Boundaries</strong> — Without crushing their
              confidence
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- PHASE 3 -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-yellow-50 to-amber-100 p-8 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-yellow-600 mb-8"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            🟡 PHASE 3: Real-World Skills (16 Weeks - 6 Months)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 font-semibold">
            From Home Success to Neighborhood Mastery
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6">
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Loose Leash Walking That Works</strong> — In chaos, distractions,
              and real-world environments
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Real-World Scenario Training</strong> — Joggers, dogs, kids,
              cars, unexpected triggers
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>The Stop-and-Go Technique</strong> — The ONLY method that
              creates willing compliance
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Generalization Training</strong> — How to make skills work
              everywhere
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Adolescent Brain Management</strong> — Preparing for the regression
              that comes at 6+ months
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- SPECIAL SECTIONS -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-100 to-pink-100 p-10 rounded-2xl border-2 border-purple-300 mb-12"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">
            ⭐ SPECIAL BONUS SECTIONS
          </h3>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">🧠 Handler Insights</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4">
                The real truths no one tells you:
              </p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-800 ml-4">
                <li>• Your nervous system affects their behavior</li>
                <li>• The 3:1 Rule (recovery from bad exposures)</li>
                <li>• Why progress isn't linear</li>
                <li>• Games teach faster than drills</li>
                <li>• Socialization ≠ forcing exposure</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                🚨 Real-World Scenarios
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4">
                Step-by-step solutions for actual situations:
              </p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-800 ml-4">
                <li>• First week home (nervous puppy)</li>
                <li>• First neighborhood walk</li>
                <li>• Dogs approaching on sidewalk</li>
                <li>• Surprise triggers</li>
                <li>• Managing barrier frustration</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                🆘 Troubleshooting Guide
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4">
                Common problems with real solutions:
              </p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-800 ml-4">
                <li>• Jumping on people</li>
                <li>• Won't come when called</li>
                <li>• Nipping/mouthing</li>
                <li>• Fearful behavior</li>
                <li>• Excessive barking</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">📅 Quick Reference</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4">
                Fast lookup guides you'll use daily:
              </p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-800 ml-4">
                <li>• Training timeline by age</li>
                <li>• Problem behavior chart</li>
                <li>• Game instructions</li>
                <li>• Golden rules (do's & don'ts)</li>
                <li>• Final wisdom section</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- KEY TOPICS -->
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">
          All The Topics You'll Master
        </h3>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Preventing Separation Anxiety
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Calm Feeding Routines & Structure
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Crate Training Done Right
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Loose Leash Walking Mastery
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Nervous System Regulation
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Bite Inhibition & Mouthing
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Recall That Works Everywhere
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Fear & Anxiety Management
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Socialization (The Right Way)
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Game-Based Training Games
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Handling Real-World Scenarios
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ Troubleshooting Common Issues
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-gray-50 py-16 px-8 rounded-2xl">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
          This Guide Is For You If...
        </h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You just brought home a puppy</strong> (or you're about to)
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You want to do this RIGHT</strong> from the beginning
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You're tired of conflicting advice</strong> online
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You want a calm puppy</strong> — not just an obedient one
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You want to prevent behavior problems</strong> before they start
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You're willing to invest time now</strong> to avoid problems
              later
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-500 p-8 rounded-xl text-center"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-900 mb-2">
            <strong>This is NOT for you if:</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            You're looking for quick fixes, shortcuts, or a guide that promises
            training in 5 minutes a day. This is real work with real results —
            the kind that last a lifetime.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DOWNLOAD SECTION -->
